Let me give you a scenario:  
You want to create an application using `stage.UNDECORATED`, however you still want all the functionalities (possibly more). To do this I found 2 approaches:  

 1. You create a fxml file with multiple panes on the sides. (kinda like this: https://github.com/goxr3plus/FX-BorderlessScene/blob/master/resources/fxml/Borderless.fxml). This allows you to control each side based on the location of those panes. 
 2. You calculate the boundaries and use no extra panes.

I&#39;ve been told that using calculations is a better way to do it, however I have my doubts. When using option 1 you don&#39;t need to continuously perform checks.

Let me use some code to clarify:  

    private Direction checkBound(double x, double y, double minX, double minY, double maxY, double maxX) {
    		if (x &gt;= minX &amp;&amp; x &lt;= (minX + bound) &amp;&amp; y &gt;= minY &amp;&amp; y &lt;= (minY + bound)) {
    			// Left Top
    			return Direction.NW;
    		}
    		else if (x &gt;= minX &amp;&amp; x &lt;= (minX + bound) &amp;&amp; y &lt;= maxY &amp;&amp; y &gt;= (maxY - bound)) {
    			// Left Bottom
    			return Direction.SW;
    		}
    		else if (x &lt;= maxX &amp;&amp; x &gt;= (maxX - bound) &amp;&amp; y &gt;= minY &amp;&amp; y &lt;= (minY + bound)) {
    			// Right Top
    			return Direction.NE;
    		}
    		else if (x &lt;= maxX &amp;&amp; x &gt;= (maxX - bound) &amp;&amp; y &lt;= maxY &amp;&amp; y &gt;= (maxY - bound)) {
    			// Right Bottom
    			return Direction.SE;
    		}
    		else if (x &gt;= minX &amp;&amp; x &lt;= (minX + bound) &amp;&amp; y &gt;= minY &amp;&amp; y &lt;= maxY) {
    			// left
    			return Direction.W;
    		}
    		else if (x &lt;= maxX &amp;&amp; x &gt;= (maxX - bound) &amp;&amp; y &gt;= minY &amp;&amp; y &lt;= maxY) {
    			// right
    			return Direction.E;
    		}
    		else if (x &gt;= minX &amp;&amp; x &lt;= maxX &amp;&amp; y &gt;= minY &amp;&amp; y &lt;= (minY + bound)) {
    			// top &amp; BOTTOM
    			return Direction.N;
    		}
    		else if (x &gt;= minX &amp;&amp; x &lt;= maxX &amp;&amp; y &lt;= maxY &amp;&amp; y &gt;= (maxY - bound)) {
    			return Direction.S;
    		}
    		
    		return null;
    	}

